Large language models (LLMs) are advanced AI systems trained on vast text data to understand and generate human-like language. They excel in tasks like answering questions, writing, coding, and translation, leveraging their scale (billions of parameters) and diverse datasets. Widely used in chatbots, content creation, and specialized applications, LLMs are transforming industries by automating tasks and enhancing human-AI interaction. However, they face challenges like data biases and contextual limitations. Examples include GPT, BERT, and LLaMa.

